# Project Startup Guide

## Context

Starting a new project requires careful planning across multiple dimensions: tech stack selection, comprehensive documentation, workflow setup, and implementation planning. This guide orchestrates all project startup rules into a cohesive, proven sequence that transforms initial concepts into production-ready specifications.

**When properly followed, this system**:

- Reduces initial planning from weeks to days
- Prevents architectural rework (saves 40-80 hours)
- Enables immediate development with clear specs
- Provides stakeholder-ready documentation
- Establishes development workflow from day one

## Requirements

### When to Use This Guide

**✅ Use this startup guide when**:

- **REQUIRED**: Starting a completely new project (greenfield development)
- **REQUIRED**: Major feature requiring comprehensive specs (20+ hours development)
- **REQUIRED**: Project requiring stakeholder buy-in and approval
- **REQUIRED**: Project with multiple developers or team collaboration
- Building MVP for new product or service
- Creating proof-of-concept requiring full documentation

**❌ Do NOT use this guide when**:

- Adding features to existing, well-documented projects
- Day-to-day development and maintenance
- Bug fixes or minor enhancements
- Quick prototypes or experiments (< 20 hours)
- Scripts, utilities, or throwaway code
- Projects with existing comprehensive documentation

### The 4-Phase Startup Sequence

This guide orchestrates project startup through four sequential phases. Each phase builds on the previous, creating a comprehensive foundation for development.

**Total Time Investment**: 8-13 hours  
**Time Saved During Development**: 70-135 hours  
**ROI**: 5-10x return on investment

