## Phase 4: Implementation Planning (1-2 hours)

### Purpose

Break down the comprehensive specifications into actionable phases with clear milestones, success criteria, and risk mitigation strategies.

### Process

**Step 1: Review Implementation Roadmap** (20 minutes)

Review `docs/14-implementation-roadmap.md` from Phase 2:

- Phases and milestones
- Feature priorities
- Dependencies
- Timeline estimates

**Step 2: Create Detailed Phase Plan** (40-60 minutes)

Use **@801-implementation-plan.mdc** to create detailed plan for Phase 1 (MVP):

```markdown
# Implementation Plan - Phase 1: MVP

## Phase Information

| Field             | Description        |
| ----------------- | ------------------ |
| Phase Name        | MVP Core Features  |
| Priority          | High               |
| Start Date        | [Date]             |
| Target Completion | [Date + 4-6 weeks] |
| Team Lead         | [Name]             |

## Features in This Phase

1. User authentication and accounts
2. Core feature 1 [from user stories]
3. Core feature 2 [from user stories]
4. Basic admin dashboard

## Implementation Steps

### Week 1: Foundation

- [x] Set up development environment
- [x] Initialize database with Prisma schema
- [ ] Implement authentication (Auth0/NextAuth)
- [ ] Create base UI components
- [ ] Set up testing infrastructure

### Week 2-3: Core Features

- [ ] Implement feature 1 (3 user stories)
- [ ] Implement feature 2 (4 user stories)
- [ ] Write tests (aim for 80% coverage)
- [ ] API documentation (OpenAPI spec)

### Week 4: Admin & Polish

- [ ] Admin dashboard
- [ ] Error handling and logging
- [ ] Performance optimization
- [ ] Security audit

## Risk Assessment

| Risk                          | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation                                        |
| ----------------------------- | ---------- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------- |
| Auth integration takes longer | Medium     | High   | Use managed service (Auth0), allocate buffer time |
| Database schema changes       | Low        | Medium | Use migrations, version control schema            |

## Testing Strategy

- Unit tests: All business logic functions
- Integration tests: API endpoints with database
- E2E tests: Critical user journeys
- Manual testing: UI/UX flows

## Success Criteria

- [ ] All MVP user stories implemented
- [ ] 80%+ test coverage
- [ ] All API endpoints documented
- [ ] Performance: < 2s page load
- [ ] Security: No critical vulnerabilities
- [ ] Deployed to staging environment
```

**Step 3: Set Up Project Tracking** (10 minutes)

Choose project management tool:

- GitHub Projects (free, integrated)
- Linear (developer-friendly)
- Jira (enterprise)

Create issues/tickets from user stories:

